"```sql\nSELECT publisher.publisher_name\nFROM superhero\nJOIN hero_attribute ON superhero.id = hero_attribute.hero_id\nJOIN attribute ON hero_attribute.attribute_id = attribute.id\nJOIN publisher ON superhero.publisher_id = publisher.id\nWHERE attribute.attribute_name = 'Speed'\nORDER BY hero_attribute.attribute_value ASC\nLIMIT 1;\n```\n\nThis SQL query finds the publisher of the superhero with the lowest speed attribute value. It joins the necessary tables based on the foreign key relationships and orders the results by the speed attribute value in ascending order, selecting the first result to get the slowest superhero."